The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal tree decompositions of graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents a simpler algorithm for this problem, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in several subfields of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with algorithmic techniques for solving a fundamental problem in graph theory. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), as the paper presents an FPT (Fixed Parameter Tractable) algorithm for the problem. The third most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), as the paper deals with combinatorial structures (tree decompositions) and their properties. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), as tree decompositions are used in geometric algorithms for solving problems such as planar graph embedding. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as tree decompositions are used in some machine learning algorithms for efficient computation of certain graph-based models.
